  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Objective: The current study examined the effectiveness of a culturally-appropriate
      adaptation of the diabetes prevention program (DPP) curriculum in reducing type 2 diabetes
      risk in Latinas with a history of gestational diabetes mellitus (GDM).

      Research Design and Methods: Seventy-six Latinas aged 18-45 years with GDM in the past 3
      years participated in an 8-week group-based, peer-educator led lifestyle intervention based
      on the DPP, with adaptations appropriate to Latino culture and recent mothers. Clinical and
      self-report indicators were assessed at baseline, post-intervention (month-3), and follow-up
      (month-6).

      Hypothesis-The modified culturally tailored DPP will improve risk factors associated with the
      development of type 2 DM.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
